\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 It's the 
\f1\b young, metal-rich stellar population
\f0\b0  category that includes Cepheid variables and Type II supernovae as distance indicators. Now that we've worked through Pop-II in detail and seen the full landscape of methods, I can give you the deeper structural picture of what Pop-I means in the H0DN framework \'97 because the category turns out to be more interesting than just "the things SH0ES uses."\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

